        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 4:59PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 459 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Hidden Valley Park, or
8 miles south of Decatur, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Frequent cloud to ground lightning and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Lightning is one of nature's leading killers. If you can
hear thunder, you are close enough to be struck by
lightning. Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding
especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Conyers, Stockbridge, Forest Park, Lithonia, Lakeview Estates,
Belvedere Park, Candler-Mcafee, Rex, Magnet, Belmont, Richardson
Park, Ellenwood, Arabia Mountain, Redan, Hidden Valley Park, Panola
Mountain State Park, Panthersville, Gresham Park, Kelleytown, and
Snapfinger.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.  Electrical
appliances should not be used unless in an emergency. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
